I"C
<p>Soldering generates some not so healthy lead fumes. A Fume extractor is a device that passes the fume through a charcoal foam which adsorbs the vapour particles and hence removes them from the air.</p>

<p>As a demonstration for my <a href="/2015/12/10/karigar/">CNC</a>, i made this simple design that uses a PVC tube with slots cut for attaching a charcoal foam piece. I have a BLDC fan on at one end to create a suction force to suck the air with fumes. The entire frame was made from MDF and hot glued and snap-fitted in place.</p>

<p><a data-flickr-embed="true" href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/94411929@N06/21354493105/in/dateposted-public/" title="Me and CNCs"><img src="https://farm6.staticflickr.com/5814/21354493105_f269a2024d_z.jpg" width="612" height="612" alt="Me and CNCs" /></a><script async="" src="//embedr.flickr.com/assets/client-code.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>

<p><a data-flickr-embed="true" href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/94411929@N06/21343818212/in/dateposted-public/" title="Me and CNCs"><img src="https://farm6.staticflickr.com/5820/21343818212_19a5576e8a_z.jpg" width="640" height="359" alt="Me and CNCs" /></a><script async="" src="//embedr.flickr.com/assets/client-code.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>

<p>The circle was cut using my CNC and the BLDC fan was fixed using 3mm nuts and bolts.There is an ON/OFF Switch as well.</p>

<p><a data-flickr-embed="true" href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/94411929@N06/20734211424/in/dateposted-public/" title="Me and CNCs"><img src="https://farm1.staticflickr.com/701/20734211424_94183de982_z.jpg" width="640" height="359" alt="Me and CNCs" /></a><script async="" src="//embedr.flickr.com/assets/client-code.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>

<p>LED lights help when soldering in dark.</p>

<p><a data-flickr-embed="true" href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/94411929@N06/21168927820/in/dateposted-public/" title="Me and CNCs"><img src="https://farm6.staticflickr.com/5702/21168927820_643eca9547_z.jpg" width="640" height="359" alt="Me and CNCs" /></a><script async="" src="//embedr.flickr.com/assets/client-code.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>

<p>It is powered using a standard 12V Wall Wart. The BLDC fan has a rating of 15V hence,the label.</p>

<p><a data-flickr-embed="true" href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/94411929@N06/20736153913/in/dateposted-public/" title="Me and CNCs"><img src="https://farm1.staticflickr.com/699/20736153913_a9e2301be5_z.jpg" width="640" height="359" alt="Me and CNCs" /></a><script async="" src="//embedr.flickr.com/assets/client-code.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>

